## Priority 2 вЂ” Core User Control & Reliability

### рџџ  P2.1 вЂ” Cancel / Stop button (with partial results saved)
**Why high:** Once a run starts, the user has no way to abort cleanly. Closing the browser orphans backends until the heartbeat watchdog kicks in. Blocks confident production use.
**Status: вњ… DONE** вЂ” Verified in code:
- `frontend/app.py`: `_request_cancel()` (lines 458вЂ“480) broadcasts `cancel` to all active backend WS connections, closes tunnels. `CANCEL_REQUESTED` flag tracked globally.
- WebSocket `cancel` action handler (lines 431вЂ“444): sends `cancel_ack`, sets state to `cancelling`.
- `backend/main.py`: `cancel` action (lines 520вЂ“529): broadcasts `cancelling`, cancels `_RUN_TASK`.
- `_run_checks_task()` (lines 311вЂ“332): `CancelledError` handler calls `_snapshot_partial_summary()`, writes to history DB with `status='CANCELLED'`, broadcasts `cancelled` event with summary + prev_checks + history_snapshot.
- `_snapshot_partial_summary()` (lines 345вЂ“365): builds ClusterResult dict from whatever sections the runner accumulated.

**Tasks:** _(all completed)_
- вњ… "Stop" button WS action `cancel`
- вњ… Frontend cancels and sends to each bastion
- вњ… Backend cancels `_RUN_TASK`, releases lock
- вњ… Partial results saved with `status='CANCELLED'`
- вњ… Frontend tunnel manager closes all tunnels on cancel
- вњ… UI shows "CancellingвЂ¦" в†’ "Cancelled" state

**Files affected:** `frontend/static/index.html`, `frontend/app.py`, `frontend/core/ws_proxy.py`, `backend/main.py`, `backend/check_runner.py`

