## Priority 3 вЂ” Highest-Leverage Feature: History & Diff

### рџџ  P3.1 вЂ” SQLite run history database
**Why high:** Single most valuable feature in the entire backlog. Unlocks diff reporting, "view last run", trend analysis, scheduled runs, and any future alerting.
**Status: вњ… DONE** вЂ” Verified in code:
- **Backend DB:** `backend/history_db.py` (233 lines) at `/opt/cloud_health/db/history.db` with WAL mode.
  - Schema: `runs`, `cluster_results`, `check_results` tables matching spec exactly.
  - Indexes: `runs(started_at DESC)`, `cluster_results(run_id, cluster_name)`, `check_results(run_id, cluster_name)`, `check_results(run_id, cluster_name, status)`.
  - `write_run()`: persists in single transaction, then prunes via `_prune(conn, max_runs)`.
  - `get_previous_checks()`: queries previous COMPLETED run for diff support.
  - `get_runs()`, `get_run()` for history queries.
- **Frontend DB:** `frontend/core/history_db.py` (154 lines) at `~/Documents/cloud_health/db/history.db` вЂ” preflight audit only (`preflight_runs` + `preflight_results`).
- `config.yaml`: `history_max_runs: 200` (line 21).
- `backend/engine/inventory.py`: `AppSettings.history_max_runs` field (line 160).
- Wired in `backend/main.py`: `history_db.write_run()` called on both COMPLETED (line 298) and CANCELLED (line 319) paths.

**Files affected:** `backend/history_db.py`, `frontend/core/history_db.py`, `frontend/app.py`, `config/config.yaml`, `backend/engine/inventory.py`

